{"TopicId":162278,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"merge option doesn\u0026#039;t work","CreatedByName":"AHeroReborn","CreatedById":173981,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T23:02:04Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"AHeroReborn","CreatedById":173981,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T23:02:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhen ever i bring in my launch vehicle to merge with a new payload, there is no green joints to place the launch vehicle on. it simply cannot be attached anywhere. try it yourself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DrLicor","CreatedById":165712,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T23:12:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt does work, the root part is the one that will be attaching.. Keep that in mind.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cpt Kerbalkrunch","CreatedById":175588,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-18T23:29:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165712-drlicor/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022165712\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/165712-drlicor/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@DrLicor\u003C/a\u003E said, the root part is what matters. Use the root tool in the \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Vehicle Assembly Building\u0022\u003EVAB\u003C/abbr\u003E to make the docking port on the launch vehicle the root part. Do the same with the payload. Now when you merge them, they\u0027ll connect together easily.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222017-06-18T23:47:21Z\u0022 title=\u002206/18/2017 11:47  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00227 yr\u0022\u003EJune 18, 2017\u003C/time\u003E by Cpt Kerbalkrunch\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHeroReborn","CreatedById":173981,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-19T00:22:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat makes a lot more sense.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso if the root part is sandwiched in between 2 other parts, it won\u0027t work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Cpt Kerbalkrunch","CreatedById":175588,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-19T00:30:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223096333\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022162278\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221497831724\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022173981\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022AHeroReborn\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 minutes ago, AHeroReborn said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthat makes a lot more sense.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nso if the root part is sandwiched in between 2 other parts, it won\u0027t work?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCorrect. Unless the connecting root part is surface-attachable and you\u0027ve got enough surface clear between the two parts to attach to.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"AHeroReborn","CreatedById":173981,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-19T00:39:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nthanks alot\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-19T06:30:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn addition, the concept is pretty much similar to subassembly, except subassembly will also reside in a seperate folder.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Nicias","CreatedById":168284,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-06-19T15:09:58Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can also use the re-root tool on the transparent non-attached sub assembly.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}